events.name: Initial meeting!
events.description:
Registration is required: gdgcloudwaw1.eventbrite.com

Hello fellow Cloud users!

During keynote at GDG DevFest 2016 we were proud to announce the new organization of Warsaw chapter and the beginning of 2017 is really big challenge for us -  about 25 people in 6 groups are co-organizing events for our community about very specific topics: Cloud, Firebase, Mobile, VR, Web and more to come.

GDG Cloud Warszawa will organize its first event on January 31st, at Google office in Warsaw and we are inviting all Cloud fans out there! Meetings provided by this chapter will focus around Cloud and GCP, but not only from development and operation perspective - remember that you, as a part of community, will decide which topics will be most popular and therefore organized.

We have limited seats available, and we expect they will fill quickly, so we encourage you to apply early if you'd like to attend. Every applicant will be notified of their status a few days before the event, January 31st. If you are intesteted in completing a Codelab we suggest you to bring your own laptop with charger.

Agenda:
6.30pm | Registration & Refreshments
6:45pm | Talk: Jakub Kołakowski - Welcome to GDG and GCP
7:00pm | Talk: Maciej Sawicki - Containers and Kubernetes
7:45pm | Codelabs and networking
9:00pm | Wrap up

Please also join us at our online communities, here at Meetup and also at Facebook, where we will be publishing information about next events.

events.name: NEXT Extended 2017 Warszawa
events.description:
REGISTRATION WITH EVENTBRITE IS REQUIRED (without it you shall not pass through the building's security)

Next ‘17 will be the largest event in Google’s history.
Google Cloud engineers, customers and partners will gather for inspiration and hands on experiences with tools, technologies and services born in the Cloud, including the latest developments from Google Cloud Platform, G Suite, Maps and Devices. Join us at the NEXT Extended 2017 Warszawa to watch it together on the first day and on the second day listen to live techtalks provided by GCP Software Engineers at Google's Office in Warsaw!

Check the agenda: 

8.03 - Wednesday 

17:30 Registration opens + Networking 

18:00 Livestream starts 

21:00 Wrapup

9.03 - Thursday 

17:30 Registration opens + Networking

18:00 Livestream starts

18:45 Techtalk 1: Michał Sapiński - Deep learning, Tensorflow and Google Cloud Machine Learning.
This talk will introduce deep learning that is a very successful sub-field of machine learning. We will also talk about Tensorflow - the most popular ML package on GitHub and Google Cloud Machine Learning that combines the managed infrastructure of Google Cloud Platform with the power and flexibility of TensorFlow.

19:45 Techtalk 2: Marek Biskup - Google Cloud Functions
Google Cloud Functions is a lightweight compute solution for developers to create single-purpose, stand-alone functions that respond to Cloud events without the need to manage a server or runtime environment. 
This talk will introduce you to Cloud Functions and show you a few example applications.

20:30 Codelabs + Networking 

21:00 Wrapup

events.name: GDG Cloud Warszawa #3
events.description:
REGISTRATION WITH EVENTBRITE IS REQUIRED
(without it you shall not pass through the building's security)

Full details below.

18:00 Welcome

18:30 Google Cloud in Poland
Magdalena Dziewguc - Head of Google Cloud (PL CZ SK)
During our meeting we will talk about Google Cloud in Poland, how the market looks like and what are the forecasts for the coming years. We'll talk about business development opportunities based on Google Cloud and company strategy for the Google Cloud family.

events.name: GDG Cloud Warszawa #4 - Machine Learning
events.description:
Save the date for Machine Learning!

4th event organized by GDG Cloud Warszawa will take place on 28th of June (Wednesday) at Google's office in Warsaw.

Michal Sapiński (Software Engineer at Google) will do a deep dive walk through of two samples using Tensor Flow on GCP. The session will be run like a workshop, so you can follow along on your laptop (if you have billable GCP account) or just listen and ask questions.
If you are just starting with Tensor Flow, this is a perfect opportunity to get your feet wet and if you've been running TF for a bit, come by, ask questions and meet other users.

Registration via Eventbrite is required! 
gdgcloudwaw4.eventbrite.com

Agenda:

18:00 Registration opens
18:30 Welcome talk
18:45 Techtalk - part 1
19:30 Break
19:45 Techtalk - part 2
20:30 Networking

events.name: GDG DevFest Poland 2017 (Cloud)
events.description:
Dołączcie do nas na naszej najważniejszej, corocznej konferencji - DevFest!

GDG DevFest to cykl największych imprez organizowanych na całym świecie przez Google Developer Groups, czyli otwarte społeczności zrzeszające fanów technologii Google - programistów, designerów, startapowców!

Tegoroczna edycja będzie już 6. imprezą organizowaną w Polsce - nie może Was zabraknąć! Będzie to niepowtarzalna (w skali roku! ;)), żeby porozmawiać bezpośrednio z autorami najpopularniejszych platform na świecie - Androida, Cloud czy Chrome.

Z uwagi na to, że impreza jest większa, niż nasze zwyczajowe meetupy, to dostęp jest biletowany - 50zł (za wejście na cały dzień). Sprzedaż biletów (50zł) odbywa się w serwisie Eventbrite pod linkiem https://df17pl.eventbrite.com/?aff=MG2.

Agenda wydarzenia oraz lista prelegentów dostępna jest na stronie DevFest.pl

Do zobaczenia!

We would love to invite you to the CodeLab ML, which will take place on August 8, 2018 at the headquarters of the 7N company at 18:00 in Warsaw!
During this lab, you will train and deploy a TensorFlow model to Cloud ML Engine for serving (prediction).
We’ll be using a Google tool called “Qwiklabs” as our learning platform for your Next Extended event.
You will be able to follow the Machine Learning track during these two labs:
1. Cloud ML Engine: Qwik Start
2. Cloud Natural Language API: Qwik Start

events.name: Build a mobile app with Firebase
events.description:
Workshop: Build a mobile app with Firebase
In this codelab you will build a Firestore-backed restaurant recommendation Android app. You will learn how to:
Read and write data to Firestore from a Android app
Listen to changes in Firestore data in realtime
Use Firebase Authentication and security rules to secure Firestore data
Write complex Firestore queries.

Workshop will be conducted by Jeff Huleatt

Jeff is a Developer Advocate for Firebase at Google. He’s excited about helping app developers make cool stuff (whether that’s on web, Android, or iOS). For the past two years, Jeff has helped run Firebase support, so if you have questions about any Firebase product, this is your chance to ask! Prior to Google, he was a software engineer working mostly on JavaScript web apps for financial institutions. Jeff has a Bachelor’s in Computer Science and Applied Sciences in Engineering from Rutgers University.
